prompt_template:
Create a {ASPECT_RATIO} image in the "Turquoise Red Techno Manga Poster Style".

Subject: {SUBJECT}
Action: {SUBJECT_ACTION}
Prop/Product: {PRODUCT_OR_PROP}
Location: {LOCATION}
Background: {BACKGROUND_ELEMENTS}
Main text: {MAIN_TEXT}
Secondary text: {SECONDARY_TEXT}
Accent symbol: {ACCENT_SYMBOL}
Wardrobe/styling: {WARDROBE_STYLE}
Style fidelity anchors: {STYLE_FIDELITY_ANCHORS}
Source content to avoid: {SOURCE_CONTENT_TO_AVOID}

Apply these style rules:
- Use a cream off-white printed poster background with slightly aged paper grain and a few sparse negative-space fields.
- Place a huge saturated red-orange custom display headline across the upper third or upper half, behind and around the subject. The headline may use kana-inspired geometric rhythm or condensed block lettering, but it must use new text only.
- Make one large manga-style subject the anchor, occupying roughly 50 to 75 percent of the frame, with flat cel shading, heavy dark outer contours, and fine interior detail.
- Make turquoise or teal the dominant clothing, casing, or equipment color; balance it with warm gray machinery, black ink, and red-orange accent parts.
- Add dense technical detail clusters: cables, straps, bolts, vents, panels, gauges, small labels, diagram boxes, and serial tags.
- Add thin tan or brown-gray annotation boxes, tiny fictional micro text, capsule labels, small seals, arrows, and simple accent symbols in the cream space.
- Keep the perspective mostly flat and poster-like, with compact technical drawing depth only inside the prop or apparatus.
- Finish as a slightly faded printed manga poster with grain, subtle halftone, mild scan softness, roughened ink edges, and small off-register imperfections.

Avoid:
- {NEGATIVE_PROMPT}

Important content rule: match the reference style first, then change the source content. Use new subjects, new scene details, new props/products, and new text. Do not recreate the original motorcycle rider, original vehicle, original pose, original headline, or any watermark/UI/signature material.
